original: Collin, Gustaf Bertil, tandläkare, Mäiriestad, f. 4/6/99 i Skara av köpm. Gustaf C. o. Anna Odhner. G. 33 m. Blenda Mathiasson. Barn: Yvonne f. 34, Lennart 38, Birgitta 44. — Stud:-ex. i Skara 17, tandl :kand. 20, tandl. 22. Assist, i Gbg 21-22, prakt, i Mariestad sed. 22, skoltandl. där 29-35, tandl. v. käkskadebehandl. å länslas. samt v. centr :fäng. o. Johannesbergs sinnesslöanst. i Mariestad. Ordf. i Västergötl. tandl :fören. 38-44, v. ordf. sed. 44, tandv:insp. i Skarab. 1. sed. 40, ordf. i Mariestads idr :haHfören. u. p. a. sed. 41, ordf. i Mariestads ten-niskl. 42-46.
translated: Collin, Gustaf Bertil, dentist, from Mäiriestad, born on June 4th, 1899 in Skara to merchant Gustaf C. and Anna Odhner. Married in 1933 to Blenda Mathiasson. Children: Yvonne (born) 1934, Lennart (born) 1938, Birgitta (born) 1944. Completed high school in Skara in 1917, graduated with a degree in dentistry in 1920, and became a licensed dentist in 1922. He worked as an assistant in Gothenburg from 1921-1922, and then started his dental practice in Mariestad. He served as school dentist in Mariestad from 1929-1935, and also worked with jaw injury treatments at the county hospital and at the Johannesberg mental hospital in Mariestad. He was chairman of the West Gothia Dental Association from 1938-1944, and vice chairman from 1944 onwards. He served as dental inspector in Skaraborg County from 1940, and was chairman of the Mariestad Sports Association from 1941. He was also chairman of the Mariestad Tennis Club from 1942-1946.
